      • createMessageFromTagValues

        IRemoteMessage createMessageFromTagValues(NameValue[] tagValues)
                                   throws RemoteException
        Creates a Message from an array of name/value pairs representing the tag/values of the message fields.

        This method allows you to create a complete FIX message with a single RMI call. This will be faster than creating an empty message using createMessageFromType(java.lang.String) and then populating its fields one by one using Message methods.

        Parameters:
        tagValues - Tag and values of fields in created message.
        Returns:
        Created message.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs
        See Also:
        createMessageFromType(java.lang.String)

      • setDoubleToDecimalConverter

        void setDoubleToDecimalConverter(IDoubleToDecimalConverter doubleToDecimalConverter)
                          throws RemoteException
        Sets the IDoubleToDecimalConverter to use when converting double values to fixed values in a FIX message. If not supplied a DefaultDoubleToDecimalConverter will be used, which does not allow any conversions.
        Parameters:
        doubleToDecimalConverter - The converter to use.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • createMessageList

        IMessageList createMessageList(NameValue[][] messages)
                        throws RemoteException
        Creates a list of messages from an array of arrays of name/value pairs.

        Each array of name/value pairs is used to create a message (as in createMessageFromTagValues(com.camerontec.catalys.util.data.NameValue[]). So the array of arrays creates a number of messages.

        The first dimension is the message number. The second dimension indexes the fields within the message.

        This method allows you to create a complete basket of orders with a single RMI call which is very fast and well suited to basket trading.

        Parameters:
        messages - Two dimensional array of tag/value pairs, representing message fields.
        Returns:
        A single object representing the list of messages.
        Throws:
        RemoteException - if a communication-related problem occurs

      • createMessage

                      throws RemoteException
        Creates a Message from a given IFIXMessage implementation. The FIX message can also contain repeating groups.
        Parameters:
        message - IFIXMessage implementation representing a FIX message to be sent over RMI
        Returns:
        Created message to send over RMI
        Throws:
        RemoteException - If any exception occurs in the RMI communication.
